Arrays 
It srores value of same datatype
1. Homogeneuous : array can only store element of same datatype 
ex (int , float , long , boolean , double( etc
2. Fixed length : size of array is always fix 
3. Memory managmenet : store element in continuous memory location 
easy to access by index;
4. Arrays in java are object themseleves and inherit from java.lang.object 
5. can store both primitive and object


======================Declaration===============
datatype arrayname [] =new datatype [size]
ex
int arr [] =new int [6]
float arr[] =new float[8]
String arr[]=new String[9]



default values 
1. int =0
2. float =0.0
3. boolean =false;
4. String =""



System.out.println(arr)
type+hashcode(address ->hexadecimal)



==========================IMPORTANT METHODS IN ARRAY=====================
1. Arrays.sort(array) ---> sort array element in acending order 
compartor applicable to object 

2. Arrays.binarySearch(array, key)
return index

3. Arrays.toString(array)

4.Arrays.equal(arr1,arr2)
compare two array their content and length

Array.fill(arra, value)
assign value to all element of array

Array.copyOf(original , size) 
create new array of given size and copy element from original to new array 
if size >original array size other elemetn would conatin deafult value

Array.copyOfRange(original , start , end)
create new array which conatin element from start to end 






==================================IMPORTANT PROPERTY===================
array.length -------> size of array 
